Rational use of oral antibiotics for pediatric infections. We carried out a survey in Japan to investigate compliance among children given oral antibiotics in an outpatient setting. The results of our survey revealed that, in Japan, approximately one-quarter of patients did not take their full course of antibiotics. Reasons for unsupervised self-discontinuation included: (1) the parent or guardian judged the infection to be cured (2) the child refused to take the drug